cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.CR 

The paper discusses machine learning methods and their limitations in handling novel situations beyond the standard i.i.d. setting. It argues that strong generalization capabilities require access to a causal model, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
